I'm running into a variable not getting renamed and colliding with an import, look like the same issue as https://github.com/rollup/rollup/issues/1550, but in that thread it said this issue is fixed in 0.47.3, but when i try version 0.48.2, the problem is still there. 

You can reproduce the bug by the following link:

https://rollupjs.org/repl?version=0.48.2&

main.js:  
```js
    import * as b from './b.js';  

    function test() {
         let test = b.test();
         let tests = b.tests();
        return test - tests;
    }
    console.log(test());`  
```

a.js:
```js
    export function test() {
        return 1;
    }
    export function tests() {
        return 2;
    }
```
 
output:
```js
(function (global, factory) {
    typeof exports === 'object' && typeof module !== 'undefined' ? factory() :
    typeof define === 'function' && define.amd ? define(factory) :
    (factory());
}(this, (function () { 'use strict';

function test$1() {
    return 1;
}
function tests() {
    return 2;
}
function test() {
     let test = test$1();
     let tests = tests(); // collide here!!!
    return test - tests;
}
console.log(test());
})));
})));

```
Thanks for your help!

~~I was unable to create a minimal repro, but [here](https://rollupjs.org/repl?version=0.52.1&) is an example of what my code does.~~(see below)

My rolled up main() looks like 
```
function main() {
  const head = head([1,2,3,4,5]);
  console.log(head);
}
```
where the `const head` identifier isn't changed, so it throws an error that head is undefined.
